<section xml:id="Revenue"   xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"><title>Investigation 5: Revenue from Theater Tickets</title>
 
<introduction><p>The local theater group sold tickets to its opening-night performance for $5 and drew an audience of 100 people. The next night they reduced the ticket price by $0.25 and 10 more people attended; that is, 110 people bought tickets at $4.75 apiece. In fact, for each $0.25 reduction in ticket price, 10 additional tickets can be sold.</p></introduction>

